2
00:00:05,076 --> 00:00:13,525
[SPEAKER_08]: On July 16th, 2022, Governor Baker signed a law, an act relative to extending certain state of emergency accommodations.

3
00:00:14,145 --> 00:00:19,050
[SPEAKER_08]: This act allows public bodies to continue holding meetings remotely through March 31st, 2023.

4
00:00:21,192 --> 00:00:30,076
[SPEAKER_08]: without a quorum of the public body physically present at a meeting location and provide adequate alternative access to remote meetings.

5
00:00:30,576 --> 00:00:42,521
[SPEAKER_08]: In accordance with this Act, this meeting of the City of Netflix Energy and Environment Committee is being conducted totally via remote participation using Zoom, including committee members and the public.

6
00:00:43,061 --> 00:00:51,552
[SPEAKER_08]: The user zoom complies with the laws requirement to provide live adequate alternative means of public access to the deliberations of public body.

7
00:00:52,273 --> 00:01:00,484
[SPEAKER_08]: Instead of holding meetings in a public place, persons who would like to listen to you to all view this meeting while in progress.

8
00:01:01,285 --> 00:01:06,068
[SPEAKER_08]: may do so by using the link that was included in the meeting agenda posted on City and Metro website.

