00:18:07,979 --> 00:18:09,120
[SPEAKER_00]: So one of the things we'll do

187
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:16,486
[SPEAKER_00]: is we ask them, you get a qualifications proposal and then a price proposal.

188
00:18:17,067 --> 00:18:28,277
[SPEAKER_00]: So first we'll look at what is it that, why are you qualified, what kind of service are you going to provide us, you know, are you going to wine and dine us or are you just going to give us like the breakfast, the freezer tray, right?

189
00:18:29,078 --> 00:18:40,425
[SPEAKER_00]: And then once you understand what they're looking to do, then we also look at the pricing and say, well, you know, your freezer tray costs as much as their wine and dining.

190
00:18:40,966 --> 00:18:56,516
[SPEAKER_00]: So like, maybe we need to go with these guys and, or, you know, your, your whining and dining is like almost as expensive as theirs is like, how can we get these pricing to come more in line with each other and, and get something better?

191
00:18:56,940 --> 00:19:03,327
[SPEAKER_00]: So it's interesting, we don't, unlike most municipal projects, we don't have to go with lowest bidder.

192
00:19:05,128 --> 00:19:09,232
[SPEAKER_00]: We actually don't legally have to put waste contracts out to bid.

193
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:12,636
[SPEAKER_00]: It's exempt from Massachusetts procurement law.

194
00:19:13,337 --> 00:19:15,539
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm sorry, why is that?

195
00:19:17,378 --> 00:19:17,918
[SPEAKER_08]: State law.

196
00:19:18,498 --> 00:19:22,819
[SPEAKER_00]: All I know, there are certain things that are exempt from Massachusetts state procurement law.

197
00:19:23,499 --> 00:19:24,879
[SPEAKER_00]: Waste contracts are one of them.

198
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:33,621
[SPEAKER_00]: I couldn't possibly speculate why, but we've decided that putting it out to bid is the right thing to do.

199
00:19:34,461 --> 00:19:39,742
[SPEAKER_00]: However, it means that we have a little bit more leeway with negotiating that we wouldn't have.

200
00:19:39,862 --> 00:19:45,543
[SPEAKER_00]: If we were building a building, we would have to go with the lowest bidder.

201
00:19:46,582 --> 00:19:58,974
[SPEAKER_00]: Assuming that the lowest qualified bidder, because this is this kind of services contract and it's a waste contract, it doesn't we don't have to go with the lowest qualified bidder.

