[SPEAKER_06]: There's, of course, there's weatherization, which we've talked about is you want to reduce the amount of work needed for a heat pump type of system.

545
00:52:50,164 --> 00:52:56,088
[SPEAKER_06]: So you insulate, you seal air, do air sealing and upgrade duct work as necessary.

546
00:52:56,108 --> 00:53:03,993
[SPEAKER_06]: And then on the right, there's the issue of electrification affecting transportation and then

547
00:53:05,593 --> 00:53:14,095
[SPEAKER_06]: Obviously, for the – where you get your electricity, you want to make it a clean, renewable energy rather than fossil fuel.

548
00:53:15,055 --> 00:53:26,637
[SPEAKER_06]: And then you've got the heating and cooling and the hot water and appliances sectors that you convert from fossil fuel to electrification using clean electricity.

549
00:53:28,038 --> 00:53:33,619
[SPEAKER_06]: Looks like there is a link at the bottom here for more information.

550
00:53:36,342 --> 00:53:49,710
[SPEAKER_06]: And you can imagine that there's quite a bit of, you know, there's methane leaks and, you know, the trouble with natural gas is natural gas, if it's leaked, is a very potent greenhouse gas.

551
00:53:50,511 --> 00:53:51,851
[SPEAKER_06]: And I'm sure there's lots of leaks.

552
00:53:53,332 --> 00:53:56,174
[SPEAKER_06]: So, that's certainly a problem.

553
00:53:58,335 --> 00:54:20,047
[SPEAKER_06]: And just the fact that you've got carbon monoxide emissions for use of natural gas, you've got inherent issues with using natural gas, both leaking of the methane and then the combustion byproducts.

554
00:54:24,723 --> 00:54:35,887
[SPEAKER_06]: There's also the cost argument for introducing electrification.

555
00:54:35,907 --> 00:54:38,348
[SPEAKER_06]: I won't go into this too much.

556
00:54:38,788 --> 00:54:49,912
[SPEAKER_06]: Certainly for electric vehicles, there might be issues about the purchase price of the vehicle, but the operational cost is certainly lower.

557
00:54:54,697 --> 00:55:07,920
[SPEAKER_06]: So in Arlington, they're looking at certainly modern electric appliances, air source, heat pumps, and also, and I think we have this in Medford, choosing a 100% clean option.

558
00:55:08,320 --> 00:55:15,581
[SPEAKER_06]: We have aggregation options in Medford as well, as Arlington looks like.

559
00:55:19,282 --> 00:55:20,822
[SPEAKER_06]: And then there's the issue of,

560
00:55:21,962 --> 00:55:36,925
[SPEAKER_06]: By 2050, we would expect that electrical generation will be predominantly non-fossil fuel in terms of the outlook here.

561
00:55:38,485 --> 00:55:50,208
[SPEAKER_06]: And the demand on the right here is also an interesting breakdown with vehicle charging being certainly a new component.

562
00:55:54,838 --> 00:55:57,800
[SPEAKER_06]: So what does Electrify Arlington offer?

563
00:55:58,380 --> 00:56:05,325
[SPEAKER_06]: They have a partnership with HeatSmart Alliance and Abode Energy Management.

564
00:56:06,966 --> 00:56:17,593
[SPEAKER_06]: It looks like, Mark, you have an issue where you can get connected with a heat pump coach by filling out the intake form.

