[SPEAKER_11]: So, I mean, I haven't seen what Mass Save provides, but I think they will just, they'll look at your house and they'll, based on looking at their, at your house as part of their Mass Save audit, they'll say, well, you know, you're a good, you're a good candidate for it or a bad candidate for doing it.

608
01:00:38,636 --> 01:00:38,696
[SPEAKER_11]: And

609
01:00:42,455 --> 01:00:46,436
[SPEAKER_11]: You can either do it with ducks or you can't do it with ducks based on your situation.

610
01:00:47,756 --> 01:00:52,597
[SPEAKER_11]: And I think they just give introductory information, which is less than we give them.

611
01:00:54,378 --> 01:01:01,080
[SPEAKER_08]: So you provide more detailed input into the energy requirements of the house as a coach?

612
01:01:02,920 --> 01:01:04,560
[SPEAKER_11]: Yeah, and it's not so much.

613
01:01:04,860 --> 01:01:11,122
[SPEAKER_11]: I mean, the energy requirements are something, but so far, I wouldn't say that that's most of what we do.

614
01:01:11,770 --> 01:01:17,191
[SPEAKER_11]: or most of what I've done, it's mostly like looking at the at the rooms in a house.

615
01:01:18,672 --> 01:01:25,714
[SPEAKER_11]: And well, if they've got ducks in their house, then you tell them, well, you can do with duck work.

616
01:01:26,694 --> 01:01:28,394
[SPEAKER_11]: And you're going to do it cheaper that way.

617
01:01:28,874 --> 01:01:31,455
[SPEAKER_11]: Or if you don't have ducks, you can do with mini splits.

618
01:01:32,615 --> 01:01:36,216
